	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Jun 12th 1:14 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Why, hello newbie. <br><br>Yes, magicians are very fun and quite powerful, however you got several things severely messed up.<br><br>First of all in duels fighting classes will focus all of their efforts on you and ignore your pet. Magicians have very low HP and so you will die. The trick about dueling as a magician is to run around faster than that fighter class(I have special methods for this), while your pet beats down on them. Eventually they will either go after the pet or just die from the pet. If they start going after the pet you nuke them, and well, thats the end of that. However, what you said about dueling is not true. Only people that don't know what they ar doing go after the pet.<br><br>Secondly, you said enchanters suck. You are SO, SO, SO wrong about this. Enchanters are SO incredibly useful, and can solo well. No, maybe their damage spells aren't that great, but at your low level you have NO idea of their immense power. They can charm, then mesmerize, they can fear, they can root, they have their own little pets, they have very useful debuffs (especially the tashan line), AND they get mana regen spells, which become very important. Any enchanter that knows what they are doing would easily kill you in a duel.<br><br>I agree with you that rogues are not that great at lower levels. Actually, IMO they are the most under-powered class that lower levels. HOWEVER, they are simply DEVASTATING once they get dual-backstab. No, I have not actually seen it, and I never had a character above level 50 when I used to play, but from what I have heard in seen in battle logs, they blow every other class out of the water in terms of damage. Not to mention that hide and sneak are very useful tools to have, especially when rogues, and only rogues know when they are working properly.<br><br>Also, you said wizards have the lowest HP in the game. That would be untrue as magicians, wizards, necromancers, and enchanters are all tied for the lowest HP in the game. However guess what, wizards did spells that let them absorb damage, and magicians don't. In that respect wizards actaully have MORE hitpoints than magicians. Actually, ALL of the pure casting classes BUT magicians get damage absorbing magic spells. So guess what newbie, MAGICIANS actually have the lowest hitpoints in the game.<br><br>Oh guess what, you forgot to talk about necromancers. Probably becuase if you have EVER interacted with one you would KNOW that they could kick your arse. I played a necromancer to level 40, and while I do LOVE magicians, the simple truth is that in a duel, the necromancer will win much more often than the magician. Yes of course it DOES depend on how good of a dueler the necromancer is, and I was able to defeat some necros in my magician-playing days, but overall necros are simply better in duels.<br><br>Hmm, lets see, you TRIED to eat clerics out saying that they can do no damage, and no nothing but heal, sucking the groups exp. up. YOU COMPLETE IDIOT! How do you think people survive when getting beat down in dungeons by monsters? BY THE DAMN HEALERS THATS HOW. A group without a healer in a dungeon usually will NOT do very well if they are deep into the dungeon. Not that you would know anything about that. My god, clerics are AWESOME, they do NOT suck up exp., they keep the party alive! And guess what else, IF you die, they can RESSURECT you, giving you exp. back from your death! So who gives a rats butt if they can't deal damage? They don't need to!<br><br>Maybe you should think about what you are saying and play the game more and at least do some research before you post garbage that its 99% untrue and completely idiotic.<br><br>Former Addict of Everquest.<br>Zuranthium Spellcrafter&lt;Elitists&gt; - Level 50 Gnome Magician of The Tribunal Server<br>Corpusnuntia Nimtathan&lt;Valorguard&gt; - Level 40 Erudite Necromancer of The Nameless Server<br>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
